 27 /* same type transforms
 28  */
 29 static void
 30 value_transform_memcpy_data0 (const GValue *src_value,
 31                               GValue       *dest_value)
 32 {
 33   memcpy (&dest_value->data[0], &src_value->data[0], sizeof (src_value->data[0]));
 34 }
 35 #define value_transform_int_int         value_transform_memcpy_data0
 36 #define value_transform_uint_uint       value_transform_memcpy_data0
 37 #define value_transform_long_long       value_transform_memcpy_data0
 38 #define value_transform_ulong_ulong     value_transform_memcpy_data0
 39 #define value_transform_int64_int64     value_transform_memcpy_data0
 40 #define value_transform_uint64_uint64   value_transform_memcpy_data0
 41 #define value_transform_float_float     value_transform_memcpy_data0
 42 #define value_transform_double_double   value_transform_memcpy_data0
 43

129 /* boolean assignments
130  */
131 #define DEFINE_BOOL_CHECK(func_name, from_member)                           \
132 static void                                                                 \
133 value_transform_##func_name (const GValue *src_value,                       \
134                              GValue       *dest_value)                      \
135 {                                                                           \
136   dest_value->data[0].v_int = src_value->data[0].from_member != 0;  \
137 } extern void glib_dummy_decl (void)
138 DEFINE_BOOL_CHECK (int_bool,    v_int);
139 DEFINE_BOOL_CHECK (uint_bool,   v_uint);
140 DEFINE_BOOL_CHECK (long_bool,   v_long);
141 DEFINE_BOOL_CHECK (ulong_bool,  v_ulong);
142 DEFINE_BOOL_CHECK (int64_bool,  v_int64);
143 DEFINE_BOOL_CHECK (uint64_bool, v_uint64);

146 /* string printouts
147  */
148 #define DEFINE_SPRINTF(func_name, from_member, format)                      \
149 static void                                                                 \
150 value_transform_##func_name (const GValue *src_value,                       \
151                              GValue       *dest_value)                      \
152 {                                                                           \
153   dest_value->data[0].v_pointer = g_strdup_printf ((format),                \
154                src_value->data[0].from_member);             \
155 } extern void glib_dummy_decl (void)
156 DEFINE_SPRINTF (int_string,     v_int,    "%d");
157 DEFINE_SPRINTF (uint_string,    v_uint,   "%u");
158 DEFINE_SPRINTF (long_string,    v_long,   "%ld");
159 DEFINE_SPRINTF (ulong_string,   v_ulong,  "%lu");
160 DEFINE_SPRINTF (int64_string,   v_int64,  "%" G_GINT64_FORMAT);
161 DEFINE_SPRINTF (uint64_string,  v_uint64, "%" G_GUINT64_FORMAT);
162 DEFINE_SPRINTF (float_string,   v_float,  "%f");
163 DEFINE_SPRINTF (double_string,  v_double, "%f");

165 
166 /* special cases
167  */
168 static void
169 value_transform_bool_string (const GValue *src_value,
170                              GValue       *dest_value)
171 {
172   dest_value->data[0].v_pointer = g_strdup_printf ("%s",
173                                                    src_value->data[0].v_int ?
174                                                    "TRUE" : "FALSE");
175 }
176 static void
177 value_transform_string_string (const GValue *src_value,
178                                GValue       *dest_value)
179 {
180   dest_value->data[0].v_pointer = g_strdup (src_value->data[0].v_pointer);
181 }
182 static void
183 value_transform_enum_string (const GValue *src_value,
184                              GValue       *dest_value)
185 {
186   gint v_enum = src_value->data[0].v_long;
187   gchar *str = g_enum_to_string (G_VALUE_TYPE (src_value), v_enum);
188 
189   dest_value->data[0].v_pointer = str;
190 }
191 static void
192 value_transform_flags_string (const GValue *src_value,
193                               GValue       *dest_value)
194 {
195   GFlagsClass *class = g_type_class_ref (G_VALUE_TYPE (src_value));
196   GFlagsValue *flags_value = g_flags_get_first_value (class, src_value->data[0].v_ulong);
197 
198   /* Note: this does not use g_flags_to_string()
199    * to keep backwards compatibility.
200    */
201   if (flags_value)
202     {
203       GString *gstring = g_string_new (NULL);
204       guint v_flags = src_value->data[0].v_ulong;
205 
206       do
207         {
208           v_flags &= ~flags_value->value;
209 
210           if (gstring->str[0])
211             g_string_append (gstring, " | ");
212           g_string_append (gstring, flags_value->value_name);
213           flags_value = g_flags_get_first_value (class, v_flags);
214         }
215       while (flags_value && v_flags);
216 
217       if (v_flags)
218         dest_value->data[0].v_pointer = g_strdup_printf ("%s | %u",
219                                                          gstring->str,
220                                                          v_flags);
221       else
222         dest_value->data[0].v_pointer = g_strdup (gstring->str);
223       g_string_free (gstring, TRUE);
224     }
225   else
226     dest_value->data[0].v_pointer = g_strdup_printf ("%lu", src_value->data[0].v_ulong);
227 
228   g_type_class_unref (class);
229 }

232 /* registration
233  */
234 void
235 _g_value_transforms_init (void)
236 {
237   /* some transformations are a bit questionable,
238    * we currently skip those
239    */
240 #define SKIP____register_transform_func(type1,type2,transform_func)     /* skip questionable transforms */ \
241   (void)0
242 
243   /* numeric types (plus to string) */
244   g_value_register_transform_func (G_TYPE_CHAR,         G_TYPE_CHAR,            value_transform_int_int);
245   g_value_register_transform_func (G_TYPE_CHAR,         G_TYPE_UCHAR,           value_transform_int_u8);
246   g_value_register_transform_func (G_TYPE_CHAR,         G_TYPE_BOOLEAN,         value_transform_int_bool);
